# Topic 72: Spark UI ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

## Why?

Suppose your Spark job normally finishes in **5 minutes**.

Today it takes **40 minutes**.

How do you find the bottleneck?

Spark UI.

---

## Concept

**Spark UI** is a monitoring tool used to analyze and troubleshoot Spark applications.

> **Simple Definition:** Spark UI shows what happened while your Spark job was running.

---

## Theory

Spark UI helps identify:

* Slow stages
* Slow tasks
* Shuffle operations
* Failed jobs
* Skewed partitions
* Resource utilization

It is the **first place to check** when a Spark job is slow.

---

## Architecture

```text
Spark Job
     │
     ▼
 Spark UI
     │
     ├── Jobs
     ├── Stages
     ├── Tasks
     ├── Executors
     └── Storage
```

---

## Important Tabs

| Tab       | Purpose                 |
| --------- | ----------------------- |
| Jobs      | Overall job status      |
| Stages    | Execution stages        |
| Tasks     | Individual task details |
| Executors | CPU & Memory usage      |
| Storage   | Cached DataFrames       |

---

## Interview Questions

### What is Spark UI?

A monitoring and debugging tool for Spark applications.

---

### Why use Spark UI?

To analyze performance and identify bottlenecks.

---

### Which tab helps identify slow stages?

Stages.

---

## Real-world Use

ETL Job

↓

Running slowly

↓

Open Spark UI

↓

Identify Stage 3 taking 90% of execution time

↓

Optimize Stage 3

---

## Common Mistakes

❌ Looking only at total execution time.

Always identify **which stage** is slow.

