# Topic 73: Adaptive Query Execution (AQE) ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

## Why?

Suppose Spark creates **200 partitions**.

After filtering,

only **10 MB** of data remains.

Spark still processes 200 partitions.

Waste of resources.

AQE solves this automatically.

---

## Concept

**Adaptive Query Execution (AQE)** allows Spark to optimize the execution plan **while the query is running**.

> **Simple Definition:** Spark automatically changes its execution plan at runtime based on the actual data.

---

## Theory

AQE can:

* Merge small partitions.
* Change join strategies (e.g., switch to Broadcast Join).
* Handle skewed partitions.

Instead of following the original plan blindly, Spark adapts during execution.

---

## Architecture

```text
Query
   │
   ▼
Initial Plan
   │
   ▼
AQE
(Runtime Optimization)
   │
   ▼
Optimized Plan
```

---

## Syntax

Enable AQE

```python
spark.conf.set("spark.sql.adaptive.enabled", "true")
```

---

## Interview Questions

### What is AQE?

A Spark feature that optimizes query execution at runtime.

---

### Does AQE optimize before or during execution?

During execution.

---

### What problems does AQE solve?

* Small partitions
* Skewed data
* Better join selection

---

## Real-world Use

Large ETL

↓

Heavy filtering

↓

AQE reduces unnecessary partitions

↓

Job completes faster

---

## Common Mistakes

❌ Thinking AQE changes your business logic.

It only changes the **execution plan**.

---

# ⭐ Spark UI vs AQE

| Spark UI            | AQE                                |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Monitoring Tool     | Optimization Feature               |
| Helps find problems | Helps solve problems automatically |
| Used by engineers   | Used by Spark internally           |

